# Next.js UI quality (sceffcom-nextjs)

When changing or building **pages, layout, or components**:

1. **Design system first** — Run from repo root:
   - `python3 .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product + audience + mood>" --design-system -p "SCEFFCOM"`
   - Stack details: `python3 .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<topic>" --stack nextjs`
   Follow palette, typography, motion, and anti-patterns from the output.

2. **Match the stack** — Next.js App Router, Tailwind, Radix, `framer-motion`, `lucide-react`, `cva` / `clsx` / `tailwind-merge`. Extend; do not add parallel UI libraries without reason.

3. **Readable UI** — High contrast body copy on parchment/cream backgrounds. Fraunces for headings, Source Sans 3 for body. Focus rings, landmarks, reduced motion.

4. **21st.dev** — Dev toolbar: `@21st-extension/toolbar-next` + VS Code extension `21st-dev.21st-extension`. Run `npm run dev`, select elements, send context to the agent. Hero region: `#hero__21st`.

5. **Brand** — SCEFFCOM CONSULT: midnight institute catalogue. Navy #0B1628 + stone paper + antique gold. Cormorant Garamond + DM Sans. Editorial magazine layout — no pill badges, grain overlays, or generic AI card grids.

6. **Content** — Edit copy in `src/data/content.ts` only; use `siteContent.meta` / `src/lib/site.ts` for URLs and nav labels.
